Turkmen Panel Says 15 Died in Blast, Turkmenistan.ru Reports

-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 
2011-07-10T15:19:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-10/turkmen-panel-says-15-died-in-blast-turkmenistan-ru-reports.html
A Turkmenistan state commission
reported to President Gurbanguly Berdymukhammedov that 15 people
died in the July 7 explosion at a storage depot outside the
capital, Ashgabat, Turkmenistan.ru  reported .  The blast killed two military officers and 13 civilians,
the commission reported, according to Turkmenistan.ru, which the
government uses to distribute information. The government
previously denied any casualties.  The death toll from the explosion may be as high as 200
people, The Chronicles of Turkmenistan website  said  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Will Kennedy  at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net . 